definitions.definition: A vehicle that has two primary wheels, one behind the other, a steering handle, and a saddle seat or seats and is usually propelled by the action of a rider’s feet upon pedals .
Any similar vehicle powered by human pedaling or steered with a handlebar , regardless of the number of wheels.
A traveling block used on a cable in skidding logs .
The best possible hand in lowball .

labels: usually in compounds specifying a context

definitions.definition: A stabilizing technique in which one foot is pushed down while the other is pulled up.
The wheel : either the lowest straight (A-2-3-4-5) or the best low hand in Lowball or High-low poker.
